  "V-COLOR": {
   "name": "V-COLOR",
   "file": "verbs.zil",
   "line": 3979,
   "endLine": 4013,
   "source": "<ROUTINE V-COLOR (\"AUX\" (DEFAULT <>) FG BG)\n\t <COND (<APPLE?>\n\t\t<TELL\n\"[Sorry, the Apple II doesn't support color selection.]\" CR>\n\t\t<RTRUE>)\n\t       (<AND <NOT ,COLOR-NOTE>\n\t\t     <EQUAL? ,MACHINE ,MACINTOSH>\n\t\t     <MAC-II?>>\n\t\t<SETG COLOR-NOTE T>\n\t\t<TELL\n\"If your Mac II displays fewer than 256 colors, you probably won't get\nthe color you ask for.  Do you still want to go ahead\">\n\t\t<COND (<NOT <YES?>> <RTRUE>)>)>\n\t <CRLF>\n\t <SET FG ,FG-COLOR>\n\t <SET BG ,BG-COLOR>\n\t <REPEAT ()\n\t    <DO-COLOR>\n\t    <TELL\n\"You will get \" <GET ,COLOR-TABLE ,FG-COLOR> \" text on a \"\n<GET ,COLOR-TABLE ,BG-COLOR> \" background.|\nIs that what you want\">\n\t    <COND (<YES?>\n\t\t   <NORMAL-COLOR>\n\t\t   <SCREEN ,S-FULL>\n\t\t   <NORMAL-COLOR>\n\t\t   <SCREEN ,S-TEXT>\n\t\t   <V-$REFRESH>\n\t\t   <RTRUE>)\n\t\t  (ELSE\n\t\t   <SETG FG-COLOR .FG>\n\t\t   <SETG BG-COLOR .BG>\n\t\t   <TELL CR \"Do you want to pick again\">\n\t\t   <COND (<YES?> <CRLF>)\n\t\t\t (ELSE <RTRUE>)>)>>>"
  },
